vulnerability.name: USN-3353-2
vulnerability.description: USN-3353-1 fixed a vulnerability in Heimdal. This update provides the corresponding update for Samba.  Jeffrey Altman, Viktor Dukhovni, and Nicolas Williams discovered that Samba clients incorrectly trusted unauthenticated portions of Kerberos tickets. A remote attacker could use this to impersonate trusted network servers or perform other attacks.

statements.status_notes: Samba could allow unintended access to network services.
